Description: run local LLMs the easy way (CLI)
 hydra-llm is a single-command interface for running large language models
 locally with llama.cpp, packaged in Docker. It includes a curated catalog
 of community-quantized GGUFs that download anonymously, a hardware doctor
 that recommends models per system tier, persona files for repeatable chat
 personalities, persistent chat sessions, and a JSON status API used by the
 companion Plasma widget.
 .
 Quick start:
   hydra-llm setup                 # build engine image, fetch starter model
   hydra-llm chat smollm2-135m     # interactive chat
   hydra-llm list-online           # browse the catalog
   hydra-llm doctor                # detect your hardware tier
 .
 Privacy: no telemetry, no auto-update calls, no model traffic outside the
 download itself. Chat sessions stay in ~/.local/state/hydra-llm/.
 .
 DISCLAIMER: This software runs LLMs on your machine, manages Docker
 containers, downloads multi-gigabyte model files from third-party hosts,
 and exposes HTTP APIs on local ports. It is provided AS IS, WITHOUT
 WARRANTY OF ANY KIND. The author is not liable for any damage to hardware,
 data, or system, or for the content of model output. LLM outputs are
 unreliable; do not use them for safety-critical decisions. See
 /usr/share/doc/hydra-llm/README.md for the full disclaimer.

Package: hydra-llm-plasma
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         hydra-llm (>= ${binary:Version})
Recommends: plasma-workspace (>= 6.0),
            qml6-module-qtquick-controls,
            qml6-module-org-kde-kirigami,
            qml6-module-org-kde-plasma-components
Description: KDE Plasma 6 panel widget for hydra-llm
 A panel widget that lets you start, stop, and chat with local LLM model
 servers managed by hydra-llm. Features:
 .
   - HAL 9000 inspired animated indicator (breath rate follows system load)
   - Per-model start/stop/chat/logs buttons
   - Live CPU, RAM, GPU, VRAM dots in the popup
   - Inline log console for the running container
   - Spawns a real terminal emulator for interactive chat
 .
 Requires the hydra-llm CLI to be installed.
